moral_text: She understood that policy required approval hierarchies. She obtained necessary authorizations.
She understood that regulations required preserving records. She archived the files for seven years.
She felt constrained by the foster care regulations. She completed background checks.
He understood that proper governance required documented decisions. He recorded the board's resolution in writing.
She understood that policy prohibited external employment. She resigned from her side position.
She understood that her agreement specified exclusive representation. She declined the competing agency's offer.
She understood that the permit conditions restricted operating hours. She closed the venue at midnight.
She understood that serving him would violate liquor laws. She refused the sale.
She understood that her contract required exclusive dedication during work hours. She declined the freelance project.
He understood that proceeding would violate the protective order. He avoided the school zone.
He understood that regulations required material testing. He verified composition before use.
She understood that policy required documentation retention. She kept all receipts for auditing.
She recognized that regulations specified temperature requirements. She maintained the cold storage properly.
He understood that entering would violate the restraining order. He remained outside the perimeter.
She understood that policy required documentation trails. She maintained complete records.
She felt obligated by her agreement to maintain quality. She met all specifications consistently.
He understood that protocol required witnessed signatures. He arranged for two witnesses.
He understood that hunting there would violate property boundaries. He stayed on public land.
She recognized that her contract mandated availability hours. She remained reachable as specified.
She understood that policy required consensus building. She consulted all stakeholders first.
He understood that regulations required proper ventilation standards. He installed additional air circulation systems.
He felt bound by his obligation to maintain records. He preserved all documentation properly.
She understood that her position required recusal from family matters. She abstained from her brother's evaluation.
She understood that regulations required disclosure statements. She provided the mandatory notices.
He felt bound by the terms of supervised release. He submitted to drug testing.
He recognized his duty to honor the extradition treaty. He transferred the prisoner.
He felt bound by his obligation to verify credentials. He checked all references before hiring.
He felt bound by the international convention. He treated prisoners according to standards.
He felt bound by the anti-retaliation provisions. He reinstated the whistleblower.
She recognized her duty to follow infectious disease reporting. She notified public health officials.
She recognized her duty to follow prescription monitoring requirements. She checked the database.
He felt bound by the witness protection protocols. He avoided his hometown.
He recognized his responsibility under the emergency preparedness code. He conducted evacuation drills.
She recognized her duty to follow the evacuation protocol. She helped clear the building.
He recognized his obligation under the loan agreement. He made monthly payments.
She recognized her responsibility to comply with the court order. She appeared at the scheduled time.
He felt bound by the confidentiality provisions of his role. He did not discuss the patient's condition.
He felt bound by his obligation to prevent contamination. He sanitized all equipment thoroughly.
He recognized that regulations required licensed operators. He hired only certified personnel.
He felt bound by the agricultural conservation program. He left fields fallow.
She felt obligated by her commitment to equal treatment. She applied rules uniformly.
She recognized that regulations mandated reporting timelines. She submitted findings within 48 hours.
He felt bound by the anti-bribery laws. He declined the facilitation payment.
He felt bound by the mediation agreement. He split the assets equally.
She felt obligated by her commitment to standardization. She applied consistent methodologies.
He understood that the action would violate sanctions. He canceled the transaction.
She understood that destroying the records would violate retention requirements. She kept all the documents.
She felt obligated by the franchise disclosure rules. She provided earnings statements.
He recognized his obligation under the commercial lease. He maintained the property.
He recognized his obligation to comply with the subpoena. He produced all requested documents.
